<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.00/1421<hi rend="superscript">6/8</hi>
                        </note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-28">December 28, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Yugloslav Ambassador called and renewed his request for a statement
                            to be issued in support of General Mihailovich.</p>
                        <p>I replied, as I had stated to him on his previous visit for this purpose,
                            that the Department had taken the matter up sympathetically and I hoped
                            to see a statement issued through some source within another day or two
                            that would be in line with our original position, as expressed while his
                            King was in this country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>